Worker rushed from ladder: schwer verletzt
During the substitution of a defective exterior feeler a 51-year old worker rushed on Thursday from a ladder in Eggelsberg and hurt himself heavily.
The man from Lamprechtshausen wanted to exchange a defective heating feeler at the exterior facade of an inn
When it climbed the ladder leaned against the spout, this slipped and the man rushed onto the concrete ground
He suffered hard injuries and was brought with the rescue helicopter "Christophorus 6" into the Salzburg country hospital.
